</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D1A46813E585DE3785BEC97DA7BA3C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="D28D46CE22B3C57C613CF1DAB8056023" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. platyphyllum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="platyphyllum">Lilium brownii platyphyllum</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="04FC2C2AD207190B8336730CAF5DA281" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii subsp. var. var. platyphyllum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" subSpecies="var." variety="platyphyllum">Lilium brownii var. platyphyllum</taxonomicName>
Baker, Gard. Chron. ser. 3, 10: 225 (1891). Type not found: China, Hubei, 
<emphasis id="13C287208255FA7986FEC0ABA61248C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">A.Henry</emphasis>
s.n.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="765AA84520BD5982844AB1F6D3C61462" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="9F091524DC0C01669BFC4E5DD2B8F0AB" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium aduncum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aduncum">Lilium aduncum</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="D14981392142D32E4CC45A7E9FB26722" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium aduncum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aduncum">Lilium aduncum</taxonomicName>
Stapf in Elwes, Gard. Chron., ser. 3, 70: 101 (1921). Lectotype designated here from syntypes: China, Hubei, Ichang [Yichang] and immediate neighbourhood, San-ya-yang, May 1888, 
<emphasis id="E77662E7D9F0F406766C009C909BC22A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">A.Henry</emphasis>
4160 (lecto. K!) [K-000464659]; syntype: China, Hubei, Ichang,&quot;between the mountains and the hills&quot; received March 1886, 
<emphasis id="34D41AA74B49E3C044F361932169A98F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">A.Henry</emphasis>
514 (syn. K!) [K-000464658].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF4B2E3227DDA062FD2FBD0857E1AFB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="E6C4EBCD31F66A04B6E36524D9CBA63D" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. ferum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="ferum">Lilium brownii ferum</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName id="7539FAC2C31F2668A57CD1FEF4F0D43E" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii subsp. var. var. ferum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" subSpecies="var." variety="ferum">Lilium brownii var. ferum</taxonomicName>
Stapf in Elwes, Gard. Chron., ser. 3, 70: 101 (1921). Lectotype designated here from syntypes: China, Hubei, Ichang, &quot;Nan-to and mountains northward&quot;, February 1887, 
<emphasis id="37789B9B086E7FB28938A89510CC632C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">A.Henry</emphasis>
2047 (lecto. K!) [K-000464656]; syntype: China, Western Hubei, June 1907 to November 1909, 
<emphasis id="4D13EF25513D23B2CC9EC2CB9D38DAE6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E.H.Wilson</emphasis>
1447 (syn. K!) [K-000464657].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB8FDCEFCA6435EB4F324B645B188BB1" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="holotype">
<paragraph id="E65A37530E7266F5D6928FE0E0CB8419" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA9F5059B425D692242F9368675CFB6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">ex Japan (cultivated), Thomas Softley Ware, Hale Farm Nursery, Tottenham, London, 22 July 1885 (holo. K!) [K-000464651]. Paratype: &quot;Hort. Ware, July 1885&quot; (para. K!).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DC3037A88C48554B540B563A5B55D44B" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AB16C644962C6F7F480AF84B159588CE" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="040076DA0856ACD67BB9AED6EC955980" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
Differing from var. 
<taxonomicName id="8B0A6D7FFA9E0D717DA2ECFCB1BDDA7B" authority="brownii" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. brownii" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="brownii">Lilium brownii brownii</taxonomicName>
and var. 
<taxonomicName id="A61A253085C140815E6262CE3136ED85" authorityName="Baker, Gardeners Chronicle ser. 3 vol. 10: 225 (22 August" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Baker" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. chloraster" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="chloraster">Lilium brownii chloraster</taxonomicName>
by the dark green obovate-lanceolate to oblanceolate leaves 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="D1EBE68B9DEFF4A046F0A32279AA0D49" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 cm (vs. linear to lanceolate 0.6-1 cm wide). The leaf size also decreases and becomes more sparse towards the apex of the inflorescence than in the other varieties. Corolla colour varies in the degree of colouration from finely chestnut brown markings externally to greenish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="164F7BC8E4FE9C1E9D91760EB64D7EB1" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="60FE742FDC6FB6994A81E68892C60D66" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F668067FB4C98286373B1AC6BF5D2F87" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B3DDC8004E7228F7732D7B3E4A591BB2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">China</emphasis>
: Anhui, Fujian, Gansu, Guangxi, Guizhou, Hebei, Henan, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangsu, Jiangxi, Shaanxi, Shanxi, Sichuan, Yunnan, Zhejiang. It seems that var. 
<taxonomicName id="7E05851387996A51ACFD19F2B5AF58C8" authorityName="Baker, Gard. Chron. 24: 134 (1 August" authorityYear="1885" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium brownii var. viridulum" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="brownii" variety="viridulum">Lilium brownii viridulum</taxonomicName>
does not occur in Guandong Province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E72A227CA3F509555A7BE3081A1B63D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="C527B5CD93A1B1DA52F5E14E36915C1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="395CC21F8A2F742526D6997CE6359C61" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Growing along ravines on grassy slopes, in clearings of open forests and amongst low scrub, 100 to 1000 m alt. Flowering in June and July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
